## Build Up a Table

Let's build up a **{gt}** table from scratch. Here is a refrence schematic from the [gt](https://gt.rstudio.com/) website:

![](gt_parts_of_a_table.svg)

The 
### 1. The Basic Table

`gt()` converts a data frame into a **gt** object. 



::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code  code-fold="true"}
tbl_1 <- gt::gtcars |>
    head() |>
    select(mfr, model, year, hp, mpg_c, mpg_h) |>
    # STUB
    gt::gt(rowname_col = "mfr") |>
    # TABLE HEADER
    gt::tab_header(
        title = "gt Cars",
        subtitle = "Like mtcars, but in a different package."
    ) |>
    # COLUMN LABELS
    gt::cols_label(
        # mfr = "Manufacturer",
        model = "Model",
        year = "Year",
        hp = "Horsepower",
        mpg_c = "MPG - City",
        mpg_h = "MPG - Hwy"
    ) |>
    # STUB HEAD
    gt::tab_stubhead("Manufacturer") |>
    # TABLE FOOTER
    gt::tab_source_note("gtcars is from the gt package.")

tbl_1
```

